The paper discusses the impact of algorithms on detecting discrimination, which falls under the category of computational social science (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the need for appropriate requirements and safeguards in the use of algorithms, which relates to the sub-category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the opacity of algorithms and the need for transparency, which relates to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the tradeoffs among competing values, which relates to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
